				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \boldsymbol{g}={\left({g}_1,\cdots, {g}_n\right)}^T\sim MVN\left(0,{\sigma}_g^2K\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M6" display="inline"><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">g</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=",,"><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>⋯</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mi>T</mml:mi></mml:msup><mml:mo>~</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">MVN</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=","><mml:mn>0</mml:mn><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>σ</mml:mi><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msubsup><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13059_2019_1813_Article_IEq1.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <italic>K</italic> is a known <italic>n</italic> by <italic>n</italic> genetic relatedness matrix that can be estimated either from genotype or pedigree data. <italic>u</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub> represents individual-level environmental effects that we assume are independent across individuals but shared between the two alleles within the same individual. We assume <inline-formula id="IEq2"><alternatives><tex-math id="M7">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
