				\begin{document}$$ {e}_{il}\sim N\left(0,{\sigma}_e^2\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M10" display="inline"><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">il</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>~</mml:mo><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=","><mml:mn>0</mml:mn><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>σ</mml:mi><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msubsup></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13059_2019_1813_Article_IEq3.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. We standardize the genetic relatedness matrix <italic>K</italic> to ensure that the mean of the diagonal elements of <italic>K</italic> equals 1, or <inline-formula id="IEq4"><alternatives><tex-math id="M11">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
